{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[E]Let me run with [A]you tonight
I'll [E]take you on a [A]moonlight ride_(drum: E . A . E . A .)
There's someone I [A]used to see
But [E]she don't give a damn[A] for me_(drum: E . A . E . A .)
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_part: Pre-Chorus}
But let me [E]get to the [B]point, 
let's roll[E] another [A]joint
And turn the [E]radio [B]loud, 
I'm too a[E]lone to be [A]proud
{end_of_part}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
[E]You don't [D]know how it [A]feels
[E]You don't [D]know how it [A]feels ... to be me
{end_of_chorus}


{comment: Post-Chorus}
